[INAUDIBLE].

00:48:36.450 --> 00:48:39.480
This one, I use it, and then
I point to a certain theory,

00:48:39.480 --> 00:48:42.140
and that's why I prefer that
term and to talk about this.

00:48:42.140 --> 00:48:43.810
And autonomy is
still a muddled mess,

00:48:43.810 --> 00:48:45.322
in terms of work life and games.

00:48:45.322 --> 00:48:46.190
Can we go to that?

00:48:46.190 --> 00:48:52.570
And then the second one,
can we learn from games

00:48:52.570 --> 00:48:57.950
in the work place in general?

00:48:57.950 --> 00:49:00.966
So disregarding the
voluntaryist issue,

00:49:00.966 --> 00:49:05.880
are there ways in which we could
make life and work anonymous?

00:49:05.880 --> 00:49:08.730
Let's speak about the
autonomy one first.

00:49:08.730 --> 00:49:16.570
There is this interesting
early book, Julian Dibbell,

00:49:16.570 --> 00:49:18.520
games journalist who
now became a lawyer.

00:49:18.520 --> 00:49:21.490
Before time, he was a great
journalist in the late '90s,

00:49:21.490 --> 00:49:25.120
looking at all the online games
craze, and he wrote a book.

00:49:25.120 --> 00:49:28.466
Rape in Cyberspace, and
all these kind of books.

00:49:28.466 --> 00:49:30.215
So it was in plain
money, how he basically

00:49:30.215 --> 00:49:33.670
made a living with designing
virtual [INAUDIBLE] space.

00:49:33.670 --> 00:49:37.460
And he noticed he was one of
the first Western observers

00:49:37.460 --> 00:49:41.205
who sold gold farmers.

00:49:41.205 --> 00:49:43.080
For those who are not
familiar with the term,

00:49:43.080 --> 00:49:46.050
gold farmers are basically
people, supposedly always

00:49:46.050 --> 00:49:47.100
Chinese gold farmers.

00:49:47.100 --> 00:49:48.475
And then there
are other articles

00:49:48.475 --> 00:49:50.760
saying that's stereotyping,
because we also

00:49:50.760 --> 00:49:53.950
find in other places--
anyhow, Chinese gold farmers

00:49:53.950 --> 00:50:00.240
are people who level up
characters or win virtual items

00:50:00.240 --> 00:50:01.712
in games for a living.

00:50:01.712 --> 00:50:04.955
And so I gain a powerful
sword in World of Warcraft,

00:50:04.955 --> 00:50:08.260
and then I sell it
to other people.

00:50:08.260 --> 00:50:11.860
And usually, these kind of gold
farmers themselves don't do it,

00:50:11.860 --> 00:50:14.610
but it's other people
hiring poor people

00:50:14.610 --> 00:50:17.840
off the street in China,
young people to basically play

00:50:17.840 --> 00:50:18.590
World of Warcraft.

00:50:18.590 --> 00:50:23.521
It's day by day, and day in, day
out in 20 hour shifts or more,

00:50:23.521 --> 00:50:24.530
and just sleep.

00:50:24.530 --> 00:50:29.320
They go back and
play as a waged war.

00:50:29.320 --> 00:50:31.380
So the more gold you
play, the [INAUDIBLE]

00:50:31.380 --> 00:50:36.740
played for the virtual
gold in real money, which

00:50:36.740 --> 00:50:40.246
is a classic form of peace work
which other people, if you've

00:50:40.246 --> 00:50:42.610
ever done peace work in
an actual assembly line,

00:50:42.610 --> 00:50:46.262
so you know that's pretty
excruciating as an activity.

00:50:48.960 --> 00:50:50.900
And he found two weird things.

00:50:50.900 --> 00:50:53.630
A, he said, they were playing.

00:50:53.630 --> 00:50:55.470
They were working in this game.

00:50:55.470 --> 00:50:57.615
And according to
standard theory,

00:50:57.615 --> 00:50:59.545
the should have hated
every minute of it,

00:50:59.545 --> 00:51:00.295
working this game.

00:51:00.295 --> 00:51:03.260
But it seemed pretty
playful at times.

00:51:03.260 --> 00:51:05.080
At times, it also
seems pretty stressed.

00:51:05.080 --> 00:51:08.230
But at times, they were still
playful in that context.

00:51:08.230 --> 00:51:10.610
And then he said
the weirdest thing

00:51:10.610 --> 00:51:12.260
is when they handed
the day off, they

00:51:12.260 --> 00:51:15.780
would hop into the
internet cafe next door

00:51:15.780 --> 00:51:19.666
and play games-- the same games.

00:51:19.666 --> 00:51:22.960
And so how can
that-- I'm puzzled.

00:51:22.960 --> 00:51:25.605
I can't even make a story
to begin to make sense.

00:51:25.605 --> 00:51:27.230
Why would they do
the thing voluntarily

00:51:27.230 --> 00:51:29.080
that they were
forced to do there?

00:51:29.080 --> 00:51:34.160
Why would the forced thing
sometimes still be fun to them?

00:51:34.160 --> 00:51:36.917
And the part of the
argument, or part

00:51:36.917 --> 00:51:38.375
of the way that
you psychologically

00:51:38.375 --> 00:51:40.530
can tease that out
is say that autonomy

00:51:40.530 --> 00:51:42.880
has a lot to do with
your internal perception

00:51:42.880 --> 00:51:45.560
of the situation.

00:51:45.560 --> 00:51:47.720
That is if in the
moment you feel

00:51:47.720 --> 00:51:49.871
like this is what I
want to do, I currently

00:51:49.871 --> 00:51:51.610
feel like doing this.

00:51:51.610 --> 00:51:53.967
And so therefore, I enjoy this.

00:51:53.967 --> 00:51:55.050
This is what I want to do.

00:51:55.050 --> 00:51:56.800
You don't have to force
yourself to do it.

00:51:56.800 --> 00:51:59.400
It feels like this is a
true expression of yourself.

00:51:59.400 --> 00:52:01.555
And so therefore,
it feels autonomous.

00:52:01.555 --> 00:52:05.995
if you go to a cloister
for a six week retreat,

00:52:05.995 --> 00:52:08.370
and somebody tells you at 6:00
AM in the morning, get up.

00:52:08.370 --> 00:52:10.903
Sweet the stairs, because
that's part of your retreat.

00:52:10.903 --> 00:52:13.221
If you then think about
I actually put myself

00:52:13.221 --> 00:52:16.240
into this oyster, and
I want to do this,

00:52:16.240 --> 00:52:19.272
and I know it's a good thing--
you might still go-- mm.

00:52:19.272 --> 00:52:21.230
But you feel this is an
expression of yourself,

00:52:21.230 --> 00:52:22.813
and you still feel
that certainly this

00:52:22.813 --> 00:52:24.062
is a voluntary act.

00:52:24.062 --> 00:52:25.962
This is still an autonomous act.

00:52:25.962 --> 00:52:29.620
And you might still find
a way of getting absorbed

00:52:29.620 --> 00:52:31.440
in the activity of
[INAUDIBLE], and then

00:52:31.440 --> 00:52:33.880
you forget the fact that
you're actually tired.

00:52:33.880 --> 00:52:37.175
So the degree to which
I perceive myself

00:52:37.175 --> 00:52:41.480
that this is currently
an outflow of my goals,

00:52:41.480 --> 00:52:44.710
wants, and my
identity is chiefly

00:52:44.710 --> 00:52:47.232
responsible to whether this
is autonomous or not for me,

00:52:47.232 --> 00:52:50.970
as an experience, which is
something that [INAUDIBLE]

00:52:50.970 --> 00:52:53.135
and [INAUDIBLE],
author of [INAUDIBLE].

00:52:53.135 --> 00:52:56.920
One of the core books in
game studies [INAUDIBLE]

00:52:56.920 --> 00:52:59.890
has found where he said
even in concentration camps,

00:52:59.890 --> 00:53:02.040
people could be absorbed
in the activity.

00:53:02.040 --> 00:53:05.740
People could feel a degree
of control, voluntarism

00:53:05.740 --> 00:53:08.090
in autonomy, because
they chose how

00:53:08.090 --> 00:53:10.295
to deal with the task that
were prescribed to them.

00:53:10.295 --> 00:53:11.836
Even if they work
for the [INAUDIBLE]

00:53:11.836 --> 00:53:13.740
that lent in their
ultimate demise.

00:53:13.740 --> 00:53:15.815
So it's this what
internal stance do

00:53:15.815 --> 00:53:18.530
I take to what's my situation?

00:53:18.530 --> 00:53:22.490
So it's not that because
workplace, therefore,

00:53:22.490 --> 00:53:24.380
obligatory context,
that are therefore

00:53:24.380 --> 00:53:26.720
necessary in autonomous.

00:53:26.720 --> 00:53:28.720
It's how do I
perceive this to be

00:53:28.720 --> 00:53:34.080
an outflow of my personal self?

00:53:34.080 --> 00:53:36.195
And there's been
research, especially

00:53:36.195 --> 00:53:41.020
in education how people can
facilitate an autonomous

00:53:41.020 --> 00:53:44.190
orientation towards an activity,
even in the mandatory context,

00:53:44.190 --> 00:53:45.660
like school.

00:53:45.660 --> 00:53:48.810
There's stuff teachers can do
to tell the students, listen.

00:53:48.810 --> 00:53:50.720
I know the next
exercise is shitty.

00:53:50.720 --> 00:53:52.850
Sorry for that.

00:53:52.850 --> 00:53:56.240
Here is why doing this is still
useful and helpful for you

00:53:56.240 --> 00:53:57.816
personally.

00:53:57.816 --> 00:54:01.202
And I would ask you to do it,
because it's helpful for you;

00:54:01.202 --> 00:54:03.680
asking permission,
explaining why,

00:54:03.680 --> 00:54:07.330
acknowledging that it's
tedious-- all these giving me

00:54:07.330 --> 00:54:09.240
free options how
to do it, with whom

00:54:09.240 --> 00:54:11.310
to do it, how to
approach the problem;

00:54:11.310 --> 00:54:13.000
lots of ways in which
you can structure

00:54:13.000 --> 00:54:16.666
an obligatory situation to
still be autonomous [INAUDIBLE].

00:54:16.666 --> 00:54:18.821
So it's a complicated
psychological thing

00:54:18.821 --> 00:54:20.195
that has a lot to
do with what is

00:54:20.195 --> 00:54:21.920
my internal stance towards it?

00:54:21.920 --> 00:54:23.850
But there's a lot
of design things

00:54:23.850 --> 00:54:27.522
around the social
situations we still can do,

00:54:27.522 --> 00:54:28.980
which leads us to
the second thing.

00:54:28.980 --> 00:54:30.979
Is there things we can
learn from games in order

00:54:30.979 --> 00:54:33.460
